      highlights: [
        "Shared store logic handles the live listing path while the template keeps its music-first tone.",
        "Public and seller modes now use the same coherent data structure instead of split demo behaviors.",
        "Catalog actions stay real: buyers can view listings or add them to cart, sellers can jump into catalog management.",
      ],
      faq: [
        {
          question: "Can I sell both lessons and music products here?",
          answer:
            "Yes. The live catalog can present tracks, beat packs, licensing offers, lessons, and other artist services together.",
        },
        {
          question: "Will release updates still look like posts?",
          answer:
            "Yes. Updates remain social-style cards so announcements feel alive without breaking the real storefront flow.",
        },
        {
          question: "Does the template still support a strong artist identity?",
          answer:
            "Yes. The visual theme stays music-oriented while the runtime behavior is normalized with the rest of the storefront system.",
        },
      ],
      listingLabel: "Release",
    },
    classes: {
      brand: "Classes Studio",
      kicker: "Courses and guided offers",
      heroTitle: "A calm teaching storefront for programs, cohorts, workshops, and structured guidance.",
      heroCopy:
        "This rebuild keeps the studio feel of the classes template while removing the old Bootstrap-heavy drift and reconnecting it to the live store engine.",
      overviewCards: [
        {
          title: "Teaching-first structure",
          copy: "Frame lessons, workshops, and recurring programs in a way that still respects the shared listing and checkout contract.",
        },
        {
          title: "Clear next steps",
          copy: "Public buyers move through real listing and cart actions instead of dead buttons or isolated course cards.",
        },
        {
          title: "Seller preview without clutter",
          copy: "Management actions stay visible in seller mode but no longer leak into public storefront HTML.",
        },
      ],
      updatesKicker: "Studio journal",
      updatesTitle: "Program news and teaching updates",
      updatesCopy:
        "Use updates for cohort openings, new lessons, student reminders, or linked featured programs.",
      catalogKicker: "Programs",
      catalogTitle: "Live courses, workshops, and sessions",
      catalogCopy:
        "The classes template now behaves like the rest of the storefront system, while preserving a softer teaching-oriented presentation.",
      highlightsTitle: "What changed in this classes template",
      highlights: [
        "The live storefront no longer depends on the older Bootstrap divergence to feel structured.",
        "Listings, updates, and CTA behavior now match the same runtime rules as the other service templates.",
        "Seller mode stays clean by routing management work back into the canonical workspace instead of duplicating fragile controls.",
      ],
      faq: [
        {
          question: "Can this template support workshops and full programs?",
          answer:
            "Yes. Listings can represent one-off sessions, workshops, courses, cohorts, or structured recurring offers.",
        },
        {
          question: "Will buyers still use the same checkout path?",
          answer:
            "Yes. Even when the copy feels course-led, the underlying buyer flow still goes through the canonical listing and checkout routes.",
        },
        {
          question: "Does seller mode still let me manage the catalog?",
          answer:
            "Yes. Seller preview mode links directly to the catalog workspace, which remains the authoritative editing surface.",
        },
      ],
